  "text": "Yolk sac tumours (YST), or perhaps more correctly they should be named as endodermal primitive tumours, are rare and malignant germ cell neoplasms that usually occur in gonads [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . YST usually presents in young patients. The median age at the time of diagnosis is 18 years (3). YST arising in the pelvis outside of the ovary are uncommon. We present a case of widely spread YST that originated from a broad uterine in a young female, that was diagnosed and successfully treated at the Vilnius University Hospital Santariskiu Clinics (Santariškių Klinikos).",
